<span id="freeTextContainer9058057445448362973"><i>And it was the afternoon of Halloween.<br/>And all the houses shut against a cool wind.<br/>And the town was full of cold sunlight.<br/>But suddenly, the day was gone.<br/>Night came out from under each tree and spread.</i><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1569483543ra/28202767.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/><i>A Halloween Carol</i>! Love the idea, I wonder why I never read this book when I was a kid!<br/>When October approaches, I find that the best stories that put me in the &quot;Halloween mood&quot; are stories for kids; I mean, Halloween is a holiday we associate with our early years, so it&apos;s only natural that the atmos</span>
  <span id="freeText9058057445448362973" style="display:none"><i>And it was the afternoon of Halloween.<br>And all the houses shut against a cool wind.<br>And the town was full of cold sunlight.<br>But suddenly, the day was gone.<br>Night came out from under each tree and spread.</i><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1569483543ra/28202767.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br><i>A Halloween Carol</i>! Love the idea, I wonder why I never read this book when I was a kid!<br>When October approaches, I find that the best stories that put me in the "Halloween mood" are stories for kids; I mean, Halloween is a holiday we associate with our early years, so it's only natural that the atmosphere of children's books is exactly what connects us with those feelings. Pumpkin heads, mummies, witches, ghosts, and a group of kids celebrating the spookiest holiday of the year... What a treat! <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1569483543ra/28202766.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> </span>
